## 📐 MathJax Formula Examples

### Example 1: Simple Password
```
Password: "Hello1"

Entropy:
S = 6 · log₂(62) = 6 · 5.95 = 35.72 bits

Time to Crack:
T = 62^6 / 10^9 ≈ 2.3 years

Classification: Fair (40-60 bits)
Security: MODERATE
```

### Example 2: Strong Password
```
Password: "MyS3cur3P@ssw0rd!"

Entropy:
S = 17 · log₂(94) = 17 · 6.55 = 111.42 bits

Time to Crack:
T = 94^17 / 10^9 ≈ 1.8 × 10^23 years

Classification: Excellent (>= 100 bits)
Security: EXCELLENT (over a century)
```

### Example 3: Weak Password
```
Password: "123456"

Entropy:
S = 6 · log₂(10) = 6 · 3.32 = 19.93 bits

Time to Crack:
T = 10^6 / 10^9 = 0.001 seconds

Classification: Weak (< 40 bits)
Security: CRITICAL!
```

